---
description: Follow Architecture Decision Records when changing architecture, persistence, or user-facing behavior
alwaysApply: true
---

# Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)

1. **Follow existing ADRs**: When changing architecture, persistence, or user-facing behavior, read the relevant documents in **docs/adr/** and align your implementation with the decisions recorded there.

2. **Consult the index**: Before implementing features that touch those areas, check **docs/adr/README.md** for the list of ADRs and open any that apply.

3. **Superseded and partially superseded ADRs**: Before treating an ADR as authoritative, check **Status** in [docs/adr/README.md](docs/adr/README.md) and the ADR header. If status is **Superseded**, do **not** implement **historical** Decision sections; follow any **Update (current)** / **Consequences (current)** in that file, then any **Superseded by** link, then **canonical** ADRs named in the superseded doc or index. If status is **Accepted** but the ADR states that a specific detail is superseded, follow the newer cross-referenced ADR for that detail. Prefer citing **Accepted** canonical ADRs over opening **Superseded** files unless you need historical rationale.

4. **Adding a new decision**: When making a new architectural or behavioral decision, create a new ADR under docs/adr/ using the template (0000-template.md), use the next number in sequence (e.g. 0002), and update the index in docs/adr/README.md. If the decision affects how agents should work, update this rule or .github/copilot-instructions.md as needed.

5. **Conflicts**: If a requested change would conflict with an accepted ADR, either update the ADR (e.g. supersede it with a new one) or align the implementation with the ADR; do not silently contradict documented decisions.

6. **NuGet packages**: When adding or changing NuGet dependencies, follow [ADR-0013](docs/adr/0013-secure-nuget-packages.md) — avoid insecure or obsolete packages; follow [ADR-0075](docs/adr/0075-nuget-license-compatibility.md) — package licenses must be compatible with GPL-3.0-only distribution.

7. **New visualizers**: Create new visualizer content as text layer renderers (inherit TextLayerRendererBase, implement ITextLayerRenderer&lt;TState&gt;) in TextLayersVisualizer, not as standalone IVisualizer implementations. See [ADR-0014](docs/adr/0014-visualizers-as-layers.md).

8. **Layer settings**: TextLayerSettings has common props plus Custom (JSON); layer-specific settings go in *Settings.cs next to the layer; use `GetCustom<TSettings>()` in Draw. See [ADR-0021](docs/adr/0021-textlayer-settings-common-custom.md).

9. **Presets**: TextLayers configurations are stored as Presets in `presets/*.json` (one file per preset). V cycles presets; S modal: R rename, N new preset. See [ADR-0019](docs/adr/0019-preset-textlayers-configuration.md), [ADR-0022](docs/adr/0022-presets-in-own-files.md).

10. **Layer settings editing**: The S settings modal is the canonical UI for editing layer settings (common properties and Custom). **Add and remove layers** (layer count 0..`TextLayersLimits.MaxLayerCount`) is also done in the S modal, not outside it. When adding layer-editing or layer-list capabilities, implement them in the S modal, not in HandleKey or other ad-hoc places. See [ADR-0023](docs/adr/0023-settings-modal-layer-editing.md), [ADR-0070](docs/adr/0070-settings-modal-add-remove-layers.md).

11. **Layer settings discovery**: Layer settings are discovered via reflection. New settings: add *Settings.cs with properties; use [SettingRange], [SettingChoices], [Setting] where needed; register in LayerSettingsReflection.s_customSettingsRegistry. See [ADR-0021](docs/adr/0021-textlayer-settings-common-custom.md), [ADR-0025](docs/adr/0025-reflection-based-layer-settings.md).

12. **C# documentation and file organization**: Non-empty XML summaries for classes and interfaces; prefer one file per class. See [ADR-0016](docs/adr/0016-csharp-documentation-and-file-organization.md).

13. **UI text overflow**: Use IScrollingTextViewport (from IScrollingTextViewportFactory.CreateViewport()) for dynamic text (toolbar, status lines) that may exceed width; use ellipsis truncation (TruncateWithEllipsis) for static text (titles, labels). Wrap strings in PlainText or AnsiText; use AnsiText when content may contain ANSI escape sequences. See [ADR-0020](docs/adr/0020-ui-text-components-scrolling-and-ellipsis.md), [ADR-0032](docs/adr/0032-typed-display-text.md), [ADR-0037](docs/adr/0037-scrolling-text-viewport-injectable-service.md).

14. **Layer dependency injection**: Layers that need external services (e.g. INowPlayingProvider) receive them via constructor injection. Snapshot does not carry service-derived data. Layers are registered in the DI container (AddTextLayerRenderers); TextLayersVisualizer receives IEnumerable&lt;TextLayerRendererBase&gt;. See [ADR-0028](docs/adr/0028-layer-dependency-injection.md).

15. **Settings format changes**: Do not add migration logic for old settings. When schema changes cause incompatibility, backup the file with `{name}.{timestamp}.bak` and create new from defaults. See [ADR-0029](docs/adr/0029-no-settings-migration.md).

16. **Performance**: Console writes, polling, and timing must be performant. Follow [ADR-0030](docs/adr/0030-performance-priority.md) when adding console I/O, key polling, or frame-rate logic. **Main redraw and FPS overlay**: **At least ~60 FPS** performance bar for full `IVisualizationRenderer.Render` on capable hosts; main loop is not capped at ~60 Hz; optional toolbar FPS from `VisualizationFrameContext.MeasuredMainRenderFps` when `UiSettings.ShowRenderFps` is set — see [ADR-0067](docs/adr/0067-60fps-target-and-render-fps-overlay.md). Optional per-layer `Draw` timing in the S modal when `UiSettings.ShowLayerRenderTime` is set — see [ADR-0073](docs/adr/0073-layer-render-time-overlay.md). **Delta-time UI/layer motion**: use `FrameDeltaSeconds` and `DisplayAnimationTiming.ScaleForReference60` per [ADR-0072](docs/adr/0072-delta-time-display-animation.md).

17. **Shows**: Preset collections for performance auto-cycling. Stored in `shows/*.json`; Tab cycles Preset editor → Show play (if eligible) → General settings → Preset editor; S in Show play opens Show edit modal. Duration per entry: Seconds or Beats. See [ADR-0031](docs/adr/0031-show-preset-collection.md), [ADR-0061](docs/adr/0061-general-settings-mode.md).

18. **Display text types**: IScrollingTextViewport.Render, RenderWithLabel, and StaticTextViewport.TruncateToWidth, TruncateWithEllipsis accept IDisplayText. Use PlainText for unformatted strings, AnsiText when text may contain ANSI escape sequences. No implicit string conversion. See [ADR-0032](docs/adr/0032-typed-display-text.md).

19. **UI settings and palette**: Use existing components (e.g. IScrollingTextViewport) when possible. UI has configurable settings in appsettings: Title, TitleBarAppName, TitleBarPalette, UiSettings.Palette (Normal, Highlighted, Dimmed, Label, optional Background), DefaultScrollingSpeed. IScrollingTextViewport.RenderWithLabel uses label/text colors when provided. Layer numbers use UI palette. Do not add separators between UI viewports; label+value colors provide separation. See [ADR-0033](docs/adr/0033-ui-principles-and-configurable-settings.md), [ADR-0036](docs/adr/0036-title-bar-injectable-component.md).

20. **Viewport labels and hotkeys**: Do not embed hotkeys in viewport or row labels (`Label:` only). Use **LabelFormatting.FormatLabel** / **IScrollingTextViewport.FormatLabel** for punctuation; document bindings via handler **GetBindings()** and the help modal (H). See [ADR-0033](docs/adr/0033-ui-principles-and-configurable-settings.md), [ADR-0049](docs/adr/0049-dynamic-help-screen.md); [ADR-0034](docs/adr/0034-viewport-label-hotkey-hints.md) is a **Superseded** historical record only.

21. **Modal dependency injection**: Modals (device selection, help, settings, show edit) are injectable services. Define an interface, implement with constructor-injected dependencies, register in ServiceConfiguration, inject into consumers. Show methods accept only runtime parameters (e.g. consoleLock, saveSettings). See [ADR-0035](docs/adr/0035-modal-dependency-injection.md).

22. **Title bar**: The header title bar is an injectable component (ITitleBarRenderer) that renders `{appName}/{mode}/{preset}/{layer}` in a cyberpunk style. UiSettings has TitleBarAppName and TitleBarPalette for customization. See [ADR-0036](docs/adr/0036-title-bar-injectable-component.md).

23. **Scrolling viewport**: Scrolling text (ping-pong) is an injectable service. IScrollingTextEngine (data) advances scroll state; IScrollingTextViewport (render) holds state, applies label/ANSI. Use IScrollingTextViewportFactory.CreateViewport() for each scroll region. Viewport auto-resets when content changes. See [ADR-0037](docs/adr/0037-scrolling-text-viewport-injectable-service.md).

24. **Header refresh timer**: Header (device, now-playing, BPM, volume) is refreshed by a 50ms PeriodicTimer independent of audio. Scrolling text in the header animates even when no audio is playing (e.g. WASAPI loopback). Use `VisualizationOrchestrator.RefreshHeaderIfNeeded()` for header-only updates (includes `PulseBeatVisualIfDue`). See [ADR-0038](docs/adr/0038-header-refresh-independent-of-audio.md).

25. **Display width**: Use display width (terminal columns) for fitting text to viewport. Wide characters (emoji, CJK, fullwidth) occupy 2 columns. Use GetDisplayWidth, GetDisplaySubstring, PadToDisplayWidth, and DisplayWidth utility for column-based measurements. TruncateToWidth and TruncateWithEllipsis use display width. See [ADR-0039](docs/adr/0039-display-width-terminal-columns.md).

26. **Dependency injection**: Prefer constructor injection and DI registration for new components (services, UI, layers, modals). Deviate only when profiling shows DI or indirection harms performance on hot paths; document the rationale. Use singleton/scoped registrations for hot-path services. See [ADR-0040](docs/adr/0040-dependency-injection-preference.md).

27. **God object refactoring**: When refactoring ApplicationShell, AnalysisEngine, or SettingsModal, follow [ADR-0041](docs/adr/0041-god-object-refactoring-strategy.md) and the task list in [docs/refactoring/god-object-plan.md](docs/refactoring/god-object-plan.md). Mark tasks `[x]` when implemented.

28. **UI component key handling**: UI components that need both rendering and key handling use a component-specific renderer interface plus `IKeyHandler<TContext>` for a component-specific context type. `TContext` must implement `IKeyHandlerContext`; use `Handle(ConsoleKeyInfo, TContext)`. Do not add a shared renderer interface (signatures differ). Key-handler behaviour is implemented via `IKeyHandlerConfig<TContext>`; `IKeyHandler<>` is registered as open generic `GenericKeyHandler<>`, which delegates to the config. See [ADR-0042](docs/adr/0042-ui-component-renderer-keyhandler-pattern.md).

29. **Layer state store**: Per-layer animation state is held in a singleton implementing `ITextLayerStateStore<TState>` for each state type. Stateful layers inject the store for their state type (e.g. `ITextLayerStateStore<BeatCirclesState>`) and call `GetState(ctx.LayerIndex)` in Draw. TextLayerDrawContext carries only shared frame data (buffer, snapshot, palette, dimensions, layer index). New stateful layers extend the store (add `ITextLayerStateStore<NewState>` to the implementation and register it); do not add new required properties to TextLayerDrawContext. See [ADR-0043](docs/adr/0043-textlayer-state-store.md).

30. **Layer renderer state type**: Every text layer renderer inherits TextLayerRendererBase and implements `ITextLayerRenderer<TState>` (marker) so the per-layer state type is part of the contract. Stateful layers implement `ITextLayerRenderer<TheirStateType>`; stateless layers implement `ITextLayerRenderer<NoLayerState>`. See [ADR-0044](docs/adr/0044-textlayer-renderer-generic-state-type.md).

31. **Max text layers**: The global maximum number of text layers is 9, defined by `TextLayersLimits.MaxLayerCount` (Domain). Use this constant for the upper cap, defaults, and key bindings 1–9; do not hardcode 9. Add/remove layers in the S modal (0..max) per [ADR-0070](docs/adr/0070-settings-modal-add-remove-layers.md). The max is not user-editable (not in appsettings or settings UI). See [ADR-0045](docs/adr/0045-max-text-layers-constant.md).

32. **Screen dump**: Screen capture (ASCII screenshot) is provided by `IScreenDumpService`; default output is plain ASCII (ANSI stripped). Use the service for any new dump behavior; hotkey is Ctrl+Shift+E, CLI options are `--dump-after N` and `--dump-path`. See [ADR-0046](docs/adr/0046-screen-dump-ascii-screenshot.md).

33. **Key handling**: Every component/class that handles keypresses must implement `IKeyHandler<TContext>` or delegate to one. No inline key-handling logic. See [ADR-0047](docs/adr/0047-all-key-handling-via-ikeyhandler.md).

34. **Key handler bindings**: Key handlers must expose which keys they handle via the method on `IKeyHandler<TContext>` that returns bindings (key/modifiers, description, optional section). Used by dynamic help and other consumers. New handlers must implement this method. See [ADR-0048](docs/adr/0048-key-handlers-expose-bindings.md).

35. **Dynamic help**: Help screen content is driven by the active screen/view (e.g. Preset editor vs Show play). Content is assembled from handler bindings (GetBindings()) and optional blurbs; current application mode determines section order or prioritization. See [ADR-0049](docs/adr/0049-dynamic-help-screen.md).

36. **UI alignment and layout**: UI is left-aligned when possible (content + right padding). Components use space in 8-character blocks; label components default to 8 cols label + 8 cols value (overridable per case). Labels use colon after the label with no space before the value ("Label:value"). See [ADR-0050](docs/adr/0050-ui-alignment-blocks-label-format.md).

37. **Viewport as data; row components**: Single-line rows (header, toolbar, settings hint) are composed from **LabeledValueDescriptor** data (label + value getter `Func<IDisplayText>`). Use **HorizontalRowComponent** with **ScrollingTextComponent** children; set data each frame via **SetRowData(descriptors, widths)**. **IScrollingTextViewport** remains for single-cell use (e.g. TextLayersToolbarBuilder). See [ADR-0051](docs/adr/0051-viewport-as-data-layouts-compose.md), [ADR-0057](docs/adr/0057-horizontal-row-unified-single-line-rows.md).

38. **UI container and component renderer**: UI is composed from **IUiComponent** (unified tree: `GetChildren(context)` null/empty = leaf, non-empty = composite) and **IUiComponentRenderer** (recurses on composites, dispatches by type for leaves). Use **CompositeComponent** for a root or nested list of children. Region implementations (e.g. HeaderContainer, MainContentContainer) build a root CompositeComponent and call `_componentRenderer.Render(root, context)`. New regions: build a root component and call the renderer; new leaf types: extend the dispatcher. Header: **IHeaderContainer** (DrawMain, DrawHeaderOnly). Main content: **IVisualizationRenderer**. See [ADR-0052](docs/adr/0052-ui-container-component-renderer.md).

39. **IUiComponent for all UI**: All UI, including modal content, must use **IUiComponent** and **IUiComponentRenderer**. New screens, regions, and modal content are expressed as a component tree and rendered via the renderer with an appropriate RenderContext. Modal draw callbacks implement drawing by building the component tree and calling the renderer (overlay-scoped context). Existing modals may be migrated incrementally; new UI and new modals must follow this pattern. See [ADR-0053](docs/adr/0053-iuicomponent-all-ui.md).

40. **UI component state and updater**: UI component instances own their state. State is updated before render via **IUiStateUpdater&lt;TComponent&gt;** (separate updater types, dispatch by component type). Call **IUiStateUpdater&lt;IUiComponent&gt;.Update(root, context)** then **IUiComponentRenderer.Render(root, context)**. Stateful components use a stable tree (same instances each frame); use **SetRowData** on **HorizontalRowComponent** when reusing row instances. Scroll state for row cells lives on each **ScrollingTextComponent** child. See [ADR-0054](docs/adr/0054-ui-component-state-ownership.md), [ADR-0057](docs/adr/0057-horizontal-row-unified-single-line-rows.md).

41. **Scrolling text as UI component**: Toolbar row is **HorizontalRowComponent** with **ScrollingTextComponent** children; each cell owns its scroll state. Use **SetFromDescriptor** to set cell data each frame. Label formatting: **LabelFormatting.FormatLabel**. **IScrollingTextViewport** remains for single-cell use outside the tree. See [ADR-0056](docs/adr/0056-scrolling-text-as-uicomponent.md).

42. **Single-line rows unified**: All single-line viewport rows (header, toolbar, settings modal hint) use **HorizontalRowComponent** with **ScrollingTextComponent** children. **LabeledRowComponent** and **ILabeledRowRenderer** have been removed. See [ADR-0057](docs/adr/0057-horizontal-row-unified-single-line-rows.md).

43. **Layer render bounds**: Optional per-layer `RenderBounds` (normalized rectangle on `TextLayerSettings`); compositing uses clip-on-`Set` on `ViewportCellBuffer`; Mirror runs in-region. Visual edit from S modal **Render region** row. See [ADR-0058](docs/adr/0058-layer-render-bounds.md).

44. **Fill BlendOver and space cells**: Default: use `Get` char + color as **under**. Optional `FillSettings.BlendSpaceAsBlack`: when **BlendOver** and `char == ' '`, use RGB black as **under** for blending only. See [ADR-0059](docs/adr/0059-fill-blendover-space-as-black.md).

45. **Universal title breadcrumb**: The same title breadcrumb appears on **row 0** for the main header and all modals (preset-scoped vs app-settings tracks; S modal: `preset[n]:layerType` + optional focused setting id + optional `/editor` when **palette or charset** list is open). Use **ITitleBarNavigationContext** and **ITitleBarBreadcrumbFormatter**. See [ADR-0036](docs/adr/0036-title-bar-injectable-component.md), [ADR-0060](docs/adr/0060-universal-title-breadcrumb.md), [ADR-0080](docs/adr/0080-shared-charset-json-and-layer-charset-ids.md).

46. **General Settings mode**: **Tab** reaches **ApplicationMode.Settings** (after Show play when eligible). Hub UI configures app-wide settings (audio input, title bar app name, optional UI theme palette id); no text-layer visualization. **S** does not open preset/Show modals; **F** does not toggle fullscreen in this mode. See [ADR-0061](docs/adr/0061-general-settings-mode.md).

47. **Application modes (classes)**: Top-level modes are **`IApplicationMode`** implementations (Preset editor, Show play, General settings) resolved via **`IApplicationModeFactory`** from persisted **`ApplicationMode`**. Modes own main toolbar + hub/visualizer composition; **Settings** uses a **one-row header** (breadcrumb only). Tab cycling is **`IModeTransitionService`**. See [ADR-0062](docs/adr/0062-application-mode-classes.md).

48. **Uniform settings list/palette drawing**: Shared **`SettingsSurfacesListDrawing`** (scroll offset + device list) and **`SettingsSurfacesPaletteDrawing`** (palette picker + Palette setting row); General hub **`Label:value`** lines use **`HorizontalRowComponent`**. See [ADR-0063](docs/adr/0063-uniform-settings-list-and-palette-drawing.md).

49. **Test project folder layout**: Under `tests/AudioAnalyzer.Tests/`, mirror each production project’s folder structure (`Domain/`, `Application/`, `Console/`, etc.); shared test utilities in `TestSupport/` (or `Common/`); cross-cutting tests in `Integration/`. See [ADR-0064](docs/adr/0064-test-project-mirrors-production-layout.md).

50. **UI theme**: Optional `UiSettings.UiThemeId` references `themes/*.json` (`IUiThemeRepository`); optional `FallbackPaletteId` in the theme uses `UiThemePaletteMapper` for base + hub swatches; `IUiThemeResolver` resolves effective UI + title bar. General Settings hub row + `IUiThemeSelectionModal` (N = new from palette). See [ADR-0071](docs/adr/0071-ui-themes-separate-from-palettes.md); [ADR-0065](docs/adr/0065-ui-theme-from-layer-palettes.md) is superseded.

51. **BPM source and Ableton Link**: `AppSettings.BpmSource` selects **audio energy detection**, **Demo** timing, or **Ableton Link** (`IBeatTimingSource` / `BeatTimingRouter`). FFT/spectrum stay on the audio path; optional native `link_shim.dll`. See [ADR-0066](docs/adr/0066-bpm-source-and-ableton-link.md).

52. **Menu selection affordance**: Selectable hub rows and vertical lists use **` ► `** / **`   `** plus full-width **background + foreground** from **`IUiThemeResolver.GetEffectiveUiPalette()`** (`Background` with fallback, `Highlighted`). Implement via **`MenuSelectionAffordance`** and shared settings-surface drawing. See [ADR-0069](docs/adr/0069-unified-menu-selection-affordance.md).

53. **ASCII video / webcam layer**: Live video as ASCII uses **`TextLayerType.AsciiVideo`** (or the name chosen at implementation) and **`IAsciiVideoFrameSource`** in Application; Windows webcam capture lives in **`AudioAnalyzer.Platform.Windows`**; frames are not passed via `AudioAnalysisSnapshot` / `VisualizationFrameContext`. Capture off the render thread, latest-frame only, drop frames if behind. See [ADR-0074](docs/adr/0074-ascii-video-layer-and-frame-source.md).

54. **Application logging**: Use configurable logging ([ADR-0076](docs/adr/0076-configurable-application-logging.md)) — MVP: persist captured exceptions to a configurable file (complements ADR-0012 viewport errors); prefer `Microsoft.Extensions.Logging` + DI; non-blocking I/O on hot paths; later: configurable Trace/Debug/Info levels and optional extra sinks; NuGet file providers must satisfy ADR-0075.

55. **Charsets**: Reusable ordered character sequences live in **`charsets/*.json`**; layers reference them via **`CharsetId`** on layer `*Settings` (not `TextSnippets`). **Charsets** = pick **one character at a time**; **`TextSnippets`** = **whole phrase(s)** for text layers. **FallingLetters** is charset-only for its glyph pool (`AnimationMode` Particles vs ColumnRain); see [ADR-0080](docs/adr/0080-shared-charset-json-and-layer-charset-ids.md), [ADR-0081](docs/adr/0081-consolidate-matrix-rain-into-falling-letters.md).
